<item ID="1774965130" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T09:52:09-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-06T07:36:11-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >XGBoost</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >2.3 Machine learning process</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.2461538552</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.8;-0.6;0.2;-0.4;-0.6;1;-0.6;-0.4;-0.6;-0.2;-0.2;-0.4;-0.4;-0.6;-0.6;0.2;0.6;0.2;-0.2;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;0.4;-0.8;0.2;0;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;0.8;0.2;0.8;-0.6;0;-1;-0.4;-0.6;0</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >56</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Three broad steps:
* data processing
* model training
* model evaluation

Problem:
1. business problem
2. formulate as ML problem

Data preparation and preprocessing:
3. collect and label data
4. evaluate data
    * data from one or more data sources
    * form single, cohesive view of data
    * visualize, use statistics to determine if can be used for ML
    * review data for consistency and correctness (need SME: largest impact)

Model training: iterative and fluid
5. Feature engineering:  process of selecting features to train models
    * features: columns of data
    * ML algorithm use features to predict target, e.g. average number of steps taken in a week from country, sex, age
    * categorical encoding: ML algorithms need numerical data, so consider
        * turn country into multiple boolean columns
        * turn male, female into 0, 1
        * birth date -&gt; day of week, month, age
6. select and train model
    * use 80% of data to train, 20% for testing
    * choose algorithms, e.g. XGBoost
    * hyperparameters:  model parameters
    * output: trained model

Model evaluation:
7. evaluate model
    * use test data, compare target in test data, use metrics on how well model is performing
8. tune model
    * change model’s data, features, hyper parameters until find model with best results

training data:
* overfitting: performs well on training data, not on evaluation data
* underfitting: performs poorly on training data, can’t capture relationship between input and target data
* balanced
* guides corrective steps

9. deploy model: after training model</text>
