<item ID="1774965145" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T09:52:24-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-06T08:02:20-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >2.5 Machine learning challenges</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.6380952512</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-1;-1;-1;0.2;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;-0.8;-0.6;-1;-0.6;-0.2;-1;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;-0.4;-0.6;-0.8;-0.6;-0.4</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >67</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Data
* poor quality, inconsistent
* non-representative
* insufficient
* overfitting and underfitting

People
* lack of data science expertise
* cost of staffing data scientists
* lack of management support

Business
* complexity in formulating questions
* explaining models to business
* cost of building systems

Technology
* data privacy issues
* tool selection can be complicated
* integration with other systems

Managed services simplify ML
* many problems can be analyzed using existing services and without substantial ML knowledge
* can use popular models like YOLO
</text>
