<item ID="1774963426" Creator="Robert Hamrick" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T09:23:29-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-03-31T09:23:29-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >(What’s This?)</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.8000000119</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.6;-1;-0.8;-1;-0.6</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >0</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >The stamps container holds a notes that represent stamps — actions that appear in the Stamps menu and that may be applied to selected notes. The name of the note is the name of the stamp, and the text of the note is the action performed.
Notes with names in parentheses, like this note, are regarded as comments and are not treated as stamps.
To add submenus to the Stamp menu, separate the menu and submenu names by a colon. For example, the stamp “Color:red” will add an action Stamps ▸ Color ▸ red.
Stamps with names beginning with a period are not listed in menus, but may be used in actions including other stamps.</text>
</item>
</item>
<item ID="1774963427" Creator="Robert Hamrick" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T09:23:29-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-03-31T09:23:29-04:00</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >Library</attribute>
<attribute name="NeverComposite" >true</attribute>
<attribute name="OnAdd" >$Prototype=&quot;Action&quot;;</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >0.5</attribute>
